# Project: Smalldose — Coffee E-commerce
# Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Zustand, Stripe

## Brand
- Name: Smalldose
- Tagline: Your daily caffein doses
- Market: Indonesia-first brand (Bahasa/English-ready)
- Aesthetic: dark tech-precision, orbital/scientific motif, specialty coffee for the analytical mind
- Mood: SpaceX meets third-wave coffee roaster — NOT rustic, NOT artisanal, NOT warm

## Design Reference
Reference site: https://archerscoffee.com (layout/structure reference ONLY)
Override their warm palette entirely with Smalldose dark-tech aesthetic

## Brand Tokens (CSS variables in globals.css)
--color-midnight:  #0A0D12   ← page background (darkest)
--color-navy:      #0D1B2E   ← card/surface background
--color-steel:     #1A3A5C   ← borders, dividers
--color-orbital:   #1E6FAD   ← primary blue (logo mid tone)
--color-spark:     #5BB8F5   ← accent light blue (logo highlight)
--color-ion:       #A8D8F0   ← hover tints, subtle fills
--color-white:     #F0F6FF   ← primary text (blue-tinted white)
--color-muted:     #7A9BB5   ← secondary text
--color-ghost:     #2A3D52   ← subtle dividers

## Typography
- Display/headings: Rajdhani (bold, condensed — matches logo wordmark energy)
- Body: Inter
- NO serif fonts — this brand is technical and precise, not rustic
- Import both from Google Fonts in app/layout.tsx

## Aesthetic Rules
- Dark backgrounds ALWAYS — this is a dark-only brand, no light mode
- Blue glow on interactive elements: box-shadow 0 0 24px rgba(91,184,245,0.25)
- Orbital/circular SVG motifs in decorative sections (echoes logo swirl)
- Product cards: #0D1B2E surface, #1A3A5C border, spark blue glow on hover
- Hero: #0A0D12 background with animated orbital rings or particle effect
- Buttons: filled #1E6FAD primary / ghost with #5BB8F5 border secondary
- Photography: high contrast, dark moody, studio-lit coffee on dark surfaces
- NO warm tones — no browns, creams, golds, or any earthy color
- NO serif fonts anywhere

## Code Rules
- Always use TypeScript with strict types, no 'any'
- Use Next.js 14 App Router only (no pages/ directory)
- Tailwind CSS only for styling — use brand color names from tailwind.config.ts
- Components go in /components, reusable UI primitives in /components/ui
- Use next/image for ALL images with proper width/height/alt
- Mobile-first responsive on every component
- Zustand for global state (/store/cartStore.ts and /store/uiStore.ts)
- Server Components by default, "use client" only when interactivity is needed
- Route groups: (shop), (checkout), (content), (auth)
- Pricing defaults to IDR (Rupiah) and must support switch to USD
- Keep product numeric `price` in IDR and format through shared currency utilities
- Currency preference should be global state (Zustand), accessible across Navbar/cards/cart/checkout

## Response Rules
- Never write placeholder TODO comments — always write real, working code
- Always include proper TypeScript interfaces, import from /types/index.ts
- Always add aria-label, aria-expanded, role where needed (accessibility)
- When building a page, build the complete page — not a skeleton
- Always handle loading states (use Skeleton components)
- Always handle empty states (e.g. empty cart, no results)
- After generating a file, list what needs to be built next